Most of the normal cells showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Ciliated cells in fallopian tube and respiratory tract showed distinct staining. Leydig cells, neuronal cells and parts of the intestinal tract were strongly stained. Nuclear or nuclear membranous positivity was observed in a few cases.

A majority of malignancies showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Most malignant gliomas, lymphomas, carcinoids, renal and endometrial cancers along with squamous and basal cell carcinomas were negative.
